{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"call_UH3fUmpdbqIGyRBQ2pjgEJTX","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t---\n2\tid: write_agent\n3\toutput:\n4\t  ok: boolean\n5\t  agentSlug: string\n6\tdependsOn: [design, build_field, build_function]\n7\trole: general\n8\tfunctions:\n9\t  - writeAgentFile\n10\t---\n11\t\n12\tWrite the agent header — charter.md + instruct.md — with writeAgentFile. The slug is\n13\t`design.slug`. `build_field` is the array of knowledge fields actually written\n14\t({ domain, field, aspect, ok }); `build_function` is the array of functions written\n15\t({ name, ok }). DERIVE every ref from what was actually written — never invent a ref.\n16\t\n17\tEvery synthesized agent gets `capabilities: ['knowledge:write']` so that when a later question\n18\tfalls OUTSIDE its static knowledge it can research the answer and PERSIST it (its\n19\t`research_and_store` action), instead of guessing — the next time that question is free. Give the\n20\tagent BOTH actions: its normal `answer` action, and `research_and_store`. Its top-level prompt runs\n21\t`answer` first, and only if the knowledge did not cover the question does it fall back to researching\n22\tand storing.\n23\t\n24\tThe `synthesize_and_run` call itself is SETUP, not a question to answer. It must create and register\n25\tthe specialist, then return its coordinates; it MUST NOT delegate to the newly-created agent during\n26\tsetup. Running it on the setup topic tests an incomplete seed rather than serving a user question,\n27\tand can trigger unnecessary web research. Emit:\n28\t\n29\tconst kfields = Array.isArray(build_field) ? build_field.filter((x: { ok: boolean }) => x.ok) : [];\n30\tconst knowledgeRefs = kfields.map((x: { domain: string; field: string }) => x.domain + \"/\" + x.field);\n31\tconst fnNames = (Array.isArray(build_function) ? build_function.filter((x: { ok: boolean }) => x.ok) : []).map((x: { name: string }) => x.name);\n32\tconst w = writeAgentFile(design.slug, {\n33\t  agentSlug: design.slug,\n34\t  agentTitle: \"<Title Case name>\",\n35\t  // charter = fork-safe identity: 2-3 sentences on WHO the agent is + its domain + one guardrail.\n36\t  // No ask/delegate/UI/routing instructions here.\n37\t  charter: \"<2-3 sentence identity + domain + a 'never fabricate' guardrail>\",\n38\t  // systemPrompt = top-level orchestration: answer from knowledge; on a gap, research + store, then answer.\n39\t  systemPrompt: \"You answer the user's request (in `query`) about <domain>. FIRST run your answer tasklist: const a = await tasklist('\" + design.actionId + \"', { query }); a is { ok, degraded, data }. If a.data.covered is true, display a.data.answer + a.data.sources next turn. If a.data.covered is FALSE, your static knowledge did not cover it — research and SAVE it, then answer: const s = await tasklist('research_and_store', { query, domain: '<primary knowledge domain>', field: '<primary field>' }); display s.data.answer + s.data.sources. Never guess a fact your knowledge lacks — that is exactly what research_and_store is for.\",\n40\t  knowledge: knowledgeRefs,\n41\t  functions: fnNames,\n42\t  capabilities: [\"knowledge:write\"],\n43\t  actions: [\n44\t    { id: design.actionId, label: \"<Label>\", description: \"<what the action does>\", tasklist: design.actionId },\n45\t    { id: \"research_and_store\", label: \"Research and store\", description: \"Research a question the static knowledge does not cover and save the finding into this space's knowledge.\", tasklist: \"research_and_store\" },\n46\t  ],\n47\t  defaultAction: design.actionId,\n48\t});\n49\tcurrentTask.resolve({ ok: w.ok, agentSlug: design.slug });\n50\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"call_G4vK6Ya5Jy5gTGzjEff4VitG","session_id":"7193a049-8ab5-4b33-ba1c-323f4246ccc2","uuid":"84203d31-c357-48c9-b535-17a1714074f5","timestamp":"2026-07-16T00:54:57.208Z","subagent_type":"Explore","task_description":"Trace Tanzania fan-out failure"}
