{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"call_hR4iNqL7Dyj4PUYRC2qAppFi","type":"tool_result","content":"commit e68c7fe030f551a34d2290ba1bbe544f229c7b49\nAuthor: Vasilis Kefallinos <vkefallinos@gmail.com>\nDate:   Wed Jul 15 21:52:57 2026 +0300\n\n    fix(system-spaces): no web research during specialist setup; complete per-part spaces\n    \n    From the 06-tanzania scenario judge (round 4). When THING builds from user-supplied\n    material, the build was spuriously researching the web and creating an incomplete set\n    of specialist spaces. Root cause: the architect delegated to a just-created specialist\n    DURING setup, and its incomplete static knowledge returned covered:false, triggering\n    research_and_store.\n    \n    L1 prompt fixes (general principles, zero scenario literals):\n    - user-thing/thing/instruct: require a COMPLETE per-part list (no generic catch-all);\n      supplied material is the build source, not a research prompt — seed it into the\n      architect handoff, don't run a new specialist's `answer` action during setup.\n    - system-architect/architect/instruct + tasklists/synthesize_and_run/04-write_agent:\n      the synthesize_and_run call is SETUP — create + register + return coordinates; MUST\n      NOT delegate to the newly-created agent during setup (the later-question\n      research_and_store path is retained).\n    - system-appbuilder/automator/instruct: a \"missing page\" repair is a WRITE request —\n      author the page/read API, don't inventory the project.\n    - prompt-contract.test.ts: assert the no-delegate-during-setup and page-repair\n      principles (11/11 green).\n    \n    Verified by a fresh from-scratch rerun through step 2: zero fetch/webSearch yields,\n    DB rows seeded. NOT fully green — per-leg space coverage is still incomplete (the next\n    invocation's first failure).\n    \n    Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 <noreply@anthropic.com>\n\ndiff --git a/libs/core/system-spaces/system-architect/agents/architect/instruct.md b/libs/core/system-spaces/system-architect/agents/architect/instruct.md\nindex 9e1fcec..c7b3903 100644\n--- a/libs/core/system-spaces/system-architect/agents/architect/instruct.md\n+++ b/libs/core/system-spaces/system-architect/agents/architect/instruct.md\n@@ -58,14 +58,17 @@ const t = await tasklist('synthesize_and_run', {\n });\n ```\n ```typescript\n-// Turn 2 — run the freshly-built agent and show the answer. Only delegate when the tasklist\n-// ran clean (t.ok) AND the build succeeded (t.data.ok); otherwise display the reason.\n-// NEVER try to build it yourself.\n+// Turn 2 — report the build result. Synthesis is SETUP, not a user question: do NOT run the\n+// freshly-created agent on its setup topic. That tests partial seed knowledge and can cause an\n+// unnecessary research fallback. The caller runs the specialist only for a later real question.\n const built = t.data as { spaceKey: string; agentSlug: string; actionId: string; query: string; ok: boolean; errors: string };\n-const result = (t.ok && built.ok)\n-  ? await delegate(built.spaceKey, built.agentSlug, built.actionId, { query: built.query, context: {} })\n-  : { error: 'Could not build the agent: ' + (built.errors || ('tasklist degraded: ' + (t.reason ?? 'unknown'))) };\n-display(JSON.stringify(result, null, 2));\n+display(JSON.stringify(\n+  t.ok && built.ok\n+    ? { ok: true, spaceKey: built.spaceKey, agentSlug: built.agentSlug, actionId: built.actionId }\n+    : { error: 'Could not build the agent: ' + (built.errors || ('tasklist degraded: ' + (t.reason ?? 'unknown'))) },\n+  null,\n+  2,\n+));\n ```\n \n **Proceed with whatever research is available.** If `context.research` is empty, thin, or came","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"call_G4vK6Ya5Jy5gTGzjEff4VitG","session_id":"7193a049-8ab5-4b33-ba1c-323f4246ccc2","uuid":"0047c73c-7582-4930-a122-e153e485b883","timestamp":"2026-07-16T00:54:58.911Z","subagent_type":"Explore","task_description":"T