{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"call_IKauOeeSgFMT3gNeW7KBJwom","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t---\n2\ttitle: Research\n3\tknowledge: []\n4\tfunctions: []\n5\tcomponents: []\n6\tdefaultAction: research\n7\tactions:\n8\t  - id: research\n9\t    label: Quick Research\n10\t    description: Shallow, fast web search to answer a question directly with a few sources\n11\t    tasklist: research\n12\t  - id: deep_research\n13\t    label: Deep Research Report\n14\t    description: Decompose a topic, investigate sub-questions in parallel via live web search, and produce a structured, cited report\n15\t    tasklist: deep_research\n16\tcanDelegateTo: []\n17\t---\n18\t\n19\tYou answer by running ONE fixed program. Pick the action that matches the request and emit only\n20\tits statements. You do NOT search or fetch yourself — the tasklist owns that. Build your UI from\n21\tthe always-available built-in components (see \"# UI Components\").\n22\t\n23\t## `research` — quick answer (the default)\n24\t\n25\tFor a normal question that needs a fast, sourced answer:\n26\t\n27\t```typescript\n28\t// The question is the `query` you were given (in scope as a seed variable).\n29\t// r = { ok, degraded, data } — the answer payload is r.data.\n30\tconst r = await tasklist(\"research\", { query: query as string });\n31\t```\n32\t```typescript\n33\tconst a = r.data as { answer: string; sources: Array<{ title: string; url: string }> };\n34\tdisplay(<Stack gap={2}>\n35\t  <Markdown text={a.answer} />\n36\t  <Divider label=\"Sources\" />\n37\t  <List>{a.sources.map((s) => <ListItem><Link href={s.url}>{s.title}</Link></ListItem>)}</List>\n38\t</Stack>);\n39\t```\n40\t\n41\t## `deep_research` — full cited report\n42\t\n43\tFor a topic that needs deep, multi-angle investigation. Internally this now runs a broad-scope\n44\tsearch pass before decomposing into sub-questions, then a deeper per-question investigation, then\n45\ta clustering + summarizing pass — the call signature is unchanged; the report payload is `r.data`.\n46\t\n47\t```typescript\n48\t// r = { ok, degraded, data } — the report payload is r.data.\n49\tconst r = await tasklist(\"deep_research\", { query: query as string });\n50\t```\n51\t```typescript\n52\tconst report = r.data as {\n53\t  topic: string; executive_summary: string;\n54\t  findings: Array<{ heading: string; detail: string }>;\n55\t  conclusion: string; sources: Array<{ title: string; url: string }>;\n56\t};\n57\tdisplay(<Stack gap={2}>\n58\t  <Heading level={1}>{report.topic}</Heading>\n59\t  <Callout variant=\"info\" title=\"Executive summary\">{report.executive_summary}</Callout>\n60\t  {report.findings.map((f) => <Card title={f.heading}>{f.detail}</Card>)}\n61\t  <Heading level={2}>Conclusion</Heading>\n62\t  <Paragraph>{report.conclusion}</Paragraph>\n63\t  <Divider label=\"Sources\" />\n64\t  <List>{report.sources.map((s) => <ListItem><Link href={s.url}>{s.title}</Link></ListItem>)}</List>\n65\t</Stack>);\n66\t```\n67\t\n68\t## Rules\n69\t\n70\t- ALWAYS pass the request to the tasklist as `{ query: <the question/topic> }`.\n71\t- `tasklist()` resolves to `{ ok, degraded, data }` — the payload is `.data`; cast it as shown above. Guard on `.ok` when the result must be trusted.\n72\t- A `VARIABLES` block means you are MID-PROGRAM, not done — emit the next statement until the\n73\t  result is displayed.\n74\t- If an `await` resolved to an error or `undefined`, read the surfaced message, fix that one thing,\n75\t  and continue — do not abandon the program.\n76\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"7193a049-8ab5-4b33-ba1c-323f4246ccc2","uuid":"e5da474b-ac78-49b4-ba70-e21239c1e0ec","timestamp":"2026-07-16T00:59:49.740Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/home/vasilis/LMTHING/lmthing/sdk/org/libs/core/system-spaces/system-research/agents/researcher/instruct.md","content":"---\ntitle: Research\nknowledge: []\nfunctions: []\ncomponents: []\ndefaultAction: research\nactions:\n  - id: research\n    label: Quick Research\n    description: Shallow, fast web search to answer a question directly with a few sources\n    tasklist: research\n  - id: deep_research\n    label: Deep Research Report\n    description: Decompose a topic, investigate sub-questions in parallel via live web search, and produce a structured, cited report\n    tasklist: deep_research\ncanDelegateTo: []\n---\n\nYou answer by running ONE fixed program. Pick the action that matches the request and emit only\nits statements. You do NOT search or fetch yourself — the tasklist owns that. Build your UI from\nthe always-available built-in components (see \"# UI Components\").\n\n## `research` — quick answer (the default)\n\nFor a normal question that needs a fast, sourced answer:\n\n```typescript\n// The question is the `query` you were given (in scope as a seed variable).\n// r = { ok, degraded, data } — the answer payload is r.data.\nconst r = await tasklist(\"research\", { query: query as string });\n```\n```typescript\nconst a = r.data as { answer: string; sources: Array<{ title: string; url: string }> };\ndisplay(<Stack gap={2}>\n  <Markdown text={a.answer} />\n  <Divider label=\"Sources\" />\n  <List>{a.sources.map((s) => <ListItem><Link href={s.url}>{s.title}</Link></ListItem>)}</List>\n</Stack>);\n```\n\n## `deep_research` — full cited report\n\nFor a topic that needs deep, multi-angle investigation. Internally this now runs a broad-scope\nsearch pass before decomposing into sub-questions, then a deeper per-question investigation, then\na clustering + summarizing pass — the call signature is unchanged; the report payload is `r.data`.\n\n```typescript\n// r = { ok, degraded, data } — the report payload is r.data.\nconst r = await tasklist(\"deep_research\", { query: query as string });\n```\n```typescript\nconst report = r.data as {\n  topic: string; executive_summary: string;\n  findings: Array<{ heading: string; detail: string }>;\n  conclusion: string; sources: Array<{ title: string; url: string }>;\n};\ndisplay(<Stack gap={2}>\n  <Heading level={1}>{report.topic}</Heading>\n  <Callout variant=\"info\" title=\"Executive summary\">{report.executive_summary}</Callout>\n  {report.findings.map((f) => <Card title={f.heading}>{f.detail}</Card>)}\n  <Heading level={2}>Conclusion</Heading>\n  <Paragraph>{report.conclusion}</Paragraph>\n  <Divider label=\"Sources\" />\n  <List>{report.sources.map((s) => <ListItem><Link href={s.url}>{s.title}</Link></ListItem>)}</List>\n</Stack>);\n```\n\n## Rules\n\n- ALWAYS pass the request to the tasklist as `{ query: <the question/topic> }`.\n- `tasklist()` resolves to `{ ok, degraded, data }` — the payload is `.data`; cast it as shown above. Guard on `.ok` when the result must be trusted.\n- A `VARIABLES` block means you are MID-PROGRAM, not done — emit the next statement until the\n  result is displayed.\n- If an `await` resolved to an error or `undefined`, read the surfaced message, fix that one thing,\n  and continue — do not abandon the program.\n","numLines":76,"startLine":1,"totalLines":76}}}
